## Development Commands

```bash
npm install                         # Install dependencies

# Development (always use tinacms dev wrapper вЂ” starts both Tina + Astro)
npm run dev                         # tinacms dev -c "astro dev"

# Production build (tinacms build MUST run before astro build)
npm run build                       # tinacms build && astro build
npm run preview                     # Preview production build

# Tina CLI
npx tinacms dev -c "astro dev"      # Equivalent to npm run dev
npx tinacms build                   # Build admin UI to public/admin/
```

### package.json scripts (canonical)
```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "dev":     "tinacms dev -c \"astro dev\"",
    "build":   "tinacms build && astro build",
    "preview": "astro preview"
  }
}
```

## Tina CMS Configuration

### tina/config.ts вЂ” complete structure

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'tinacms'

export default defineConfig({
  branch: process.env.GITHUB_BRANCH ?? process.env.VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_REF ?? '{{GIT_MAIN_BRANCH}}',
  clientId:  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_TINA_CLIENT_ID,  // Tina Cloud
  token:     process.env.TINA_TOKEN,                   // Tina Cloud read/write token

  build: {
    outputFolder: 'admin',    // в†’ public/admin/ (served at /admin)
    publicFolder: 'public',
  },

  media: {
    tina: {
      mediaRoot: 'uploads',
      publicFolder: 'public',
    },
  },

  schema: {
    collections: [
      {
        name:   'post',
        label:  'Blog Posts',
        path:   'src/content/blog',
        format: 'mdx',
        ui: {
          router: ({ document }) => `/blog/${document._sys.filename}`,
        },
        fields: [
          { type: 'string',   name: 'title',       label: 'Title',        required: true, isTitle: true },
          { type: 'string',   name: 'description', label: 'Description',  ui: { component: 'textarea' } },
          { type: 'datetime', name: 'date',         label: 'Publish Date' },
          { type: 'boolean',  name: 'draft',        label: 'Draft' },
          { type: 'image',    name: 'hero',         label: 'Hero Image' },
          { type: 'string',   name: 'tags',         label: 'Tags',         list: true },
          { type: 'rich-text', name: 'body',        label: 'Body',         isBody: true },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
})
```

## Data Fetching in Astro

### List page

```astro
---
// src/pages/blog/index.astro
import { client } from '../../tina/__generated__/client'
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const { data } = await client.queries.postConnection({
  sort: 'date',
  filter: { draft: { eq: false } },
})
const posts = data.postConnection.edges!.map(e => e!.node!)
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog">
  {posts.map(post => (
    <article>
      <a href={`/blog/${post._sys.filename}`}>{post.title}</a>
      <time>{post.date}</time>
    </article>
  ))}
</BaseLayout>
```

### Detail page (SSG with getStaticPaths)

```astro
---
// src/pages/blog/[slug].astro
import { client } from '../../tina/__generated__/client'
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = await client.queries.postConnection()
  return posts.data.postConnection.edges!.map(edge => ({
    params: { slug: edge!.node!._sys.filename },
    props:  { post: edge!.node! },
  }))
}

const { slug } = Astro.params
const { data } = await client.queries.post({ relativePath: `${slug}.mdx` })
---

<BaseLayout title={data.post.title}>
  <h1>{data.post.title}</h1>
  <time>{data.post.date}</time>
  <!-- Render body as MDX via Astro's content collections or a custom renderer -->
</BaseLayout>
```

